  "response": "Yes, middle-class people shop at thrift stores for a variety of reasons. Here's a breakdown:\n\n*   **Saving money:** Thrift stores offer significantly lower prices compared to retail stores, allowing middle-class individuals to stretch their budget further.\n*   **Sustainability:** Many middle-class consumers are becoming more environmentally conscious and choose thrift stores as a way to reduce waste and support sustainable practices.\n*   **Unique finds:** Thrift stores can offer unique, vintage, or one-of-a-kind items that are not available in mainstream retail.\n*   **Brand names:** It's possible to find clothing, housewares, and other items from well-known brands at discounted prices.\n*   **Necessity:** For some middle-class families, thrifting can be a necessity, especially when children are growing quickly or during times of financial strain.",
